        "title": "Test Coverage Analysis",
        "content": "\nNo test suite exists anywhere in the repo — no `tests/` directory, no `pytest`/`pytest-asyncio` in `requirements.txt`, zero `test_*.py` files. All 1505 lines across 8 modules are currently unverified by automated tests. Below is a gap analysis per module, ordered by risk, with skeletons using `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio` + `httpx.MockTransport` (the codebase's own fetchers.py docstring calls this out as the intended seam).\n\nSuggested setup first:\n```python\n",
